# Build Spec — Yates-Style Training Log (React App)

**Audience:** an AI agent (or developer) tasked with building this app.
**Output:** a single React artifact, mobile-first, single-user, no auth.
**Source of truth for behaviour:** the companion file `yates_training_guide.md`. Read it first. The app's job is to make that guide *actionable in the gym*.

---

## 1. What this app is

A personal training log inspired by Dorian Yates' physical notebooks (1983–1997). Yates kept every session, every set, every rep, plus how he felt and what he ate, and used the log to:

- Spot plateaus within weeks
- Run controlled experiments on himself (change one variable, watch for response)
- Catch overtraining before it derailed progress
- Settle questions about his own history decades later
- Avoid "shooting in the dark"

The app must support all of that. It is **not** a social fitness app, a workout generator, or a coaching platform.

---

## 2. Required features (mapped to actions)

Each feature below is non-negotiable. They map 1:1 to actions a training log must support.

| # | Action | Feature |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Document workouts | Log session: date, exercises, warm-ups, working set to failure, optional drop sets, pre-exhaust pairings, per-exercise notes |
| 2 | Spot plateaus | Per-exercise progression chart (weight × reps over time); visual flag when working set hasn't progressed in N sessions |
| 3 | Monthly review + goals | Monthly view summarising last 4 weeks; set 1–3 targets for next month; track them |
| 4 | Run n=1 experiments | "Experiment marker" — log a date when something changes (e.g. "started 4×/week"). Show before/after progression on charts. |
| 5 | Memory aid / search history | Search exercises by name, filter by date range, view any historical session in full |
| 6 | Catch overtraining | Log subjective state per session (energy / sleep / stress 1–5; overall feel: strong / flat / distracted). Surface a warning if 3 consecutive sessions are flat or worse. |
| 7 | Log diet alongside training | Per-session diet notes field. Optional quick tags (low-carb, high-protein, IF window). |
| 8 | Avoid "shooting in the dark" | Dashboard with weekly adherence (sessions/week), volume per muscle group, working-set progression at a glance |

### Yates-specific behaviours to embed

- **Deload reminder:** after 5–6 consecutive "hard" weeks of training, surface a soft prompt: *"You've trained hard for 6 weeks. Consider 2 weeks submaximal."*
- **Once-per-week-per-muscle warning:** if a muscle group is logged twice within 7 days (excluding calves), show a gentle warning.
- **Failure tracking:** every working set must be marked `to_failure: true/false`. The whole system rests on this.
- **Warm-up vs working set distinction:** UI must make this distinction obvious — they are different things and analytics depend on the difference.

