## 3. Data model

Use `window.storage` (artifact storage API). Keys are hierarchical strings.

### Entities

```
Session
  id: string (e.g. "session_<timestamp>")
  date: ISO date string
  energy: 1–5
  sleep: 1–5
  stress: 1–5
  overall_feel: "strong" | "flat" | "distracted"
  diet_notes: string
  diet_tags: string[]  // optional, e.g. ["low-carb", "IF"]
  notes: string
  exercises: Exercise[]

Exercise (within a Session)
  id: string
  name: string
  muscle_group: "chest" | "back" | "legs" | "shoulders" | "biceps" | "triceps" | "calves" | "abs" | "other"
  warmup_sets: Set[]
  working_set: Set  // single working set, to failure
  drop_set: Set | null
  pre_exhaust_with: string | null  // name of paired isolation exercise, if any
  notes: string

Set
  weight: number
  unit: "kg" | "lb"
  reps: number
  to_failure: boolean

MonthlyReview
  month: "YYYY-MM"
  observations: string
  targets: Target[]

Target
  id: string
  description: string
  exercise_name: string | null
  target_metric: "weight" | "reps" | "frequency" | "other"
  target_value: string
  achieved: boolean

ExperimentMarker
  id: string
  date: ISO date string
  what_changed: string  // e.g. "Started 4×/week", "Switched to low-carb diet"
  notes: string
```

### Storage keys

```
sessions:<session_id>            → Session JSON
sessions_index                   → { ids: string[], by_date: { "YYYY-MM-DD": session_id } }
reviews:<YYYY-MM>                → MonthlyReview JSON
experiments:<id>                 → ExperimentMarker JSON
experiments_index                → string[] of ids
exercise_library                 → string[] of exercise names the user has used (for autocomplete)
settings                         → { unit: "kg"|"lb", deload_after_weeks: 6, ... }
```

Combine related data into single keys where possible (per the storage API guidance — fewer round trips).

